WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.640 --> 00:00:08.520
Tonight on "Secrets Declassified."

2
00:00:08.640 --> 00:00:11.560
the rogue missions
that broke all the rules.

3
00:00:11.680 --> 00:00:14.360
like the black op
to kidnap a Nazi war criminal

4
00:00:14.480 --> 00:00:16.160
in broad daylight.

5
00:00:16.280 --> 00:00:18.040
He's one of the most
wanted men in the world.

6
00:00:18.120 --> 00:00:21.200
and they have just one chance
to bring him in.

7
00:00:21.320 --> 00:00:25.400
Winston Churchill recruits a
boatload of modern-day pirates.

8
00:00:25.520 --> 00:00:27.480
There's fighting dirty. and then there's

9
00:00:27.600 --> 00:00:29.160
fighting like Churchill.

10
00:00:29.280 --> 00:00:31.640
And the wartime spy
who goes undercover

11
00:00:31.760 --> 00:00:34.280
in one of the deadliest places in history.

12
00:00:34.400 --> 00:00:37.160
Who's mad enough to actually
break into Auschwitz?

13
00:00:37.280 --> 00:00:39.880
These are the most extreme
and illicit missions

14
00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:41.920
ever carried out by governments
and the people

15
00:00:42.040 --> 00:00:43.080
who work for them.

16
00:00:43.200 --> 00:00:45.280
It's time to bring them to light.

17
00:00:53.840 --> 00:00:57.480
In 1960. a group of men
arrive at Buenos Aires airport.

18
00:00:57.600 --> 00:01:00.360
They look like ordinary
businessmen on a sales trip.

19
00:01:00.480 --> 00:01:02.520
In fact. they're intelligence operatives

20
00:01:02.640 --> 00:01:04.800
on a high-stakes operation:

21
00:01:04.920 --> 00:01:08.160
to kidnap a factory worker
called Ricardo Klement.

22
00:01:08.280 --> 00:01:11.240
Real name? Adolf Eichmann.

23
00:01:14.800 --> 00:01:17.720
It's been 15 years
since the end of World War II.

24
00:01:17.840 --> 00:01:19.800
and Adolf Eichmann is one of the most

25
00:01:19.920 --> 00:01:23.200
notorious Nazi war criminals
still evading justice.

26
00:01:23.320 --> 00:01:25.680
Eichmann. more so
than almost anyone else.

27
00:01:25.800 --> 00:01:28.360
is the logistical architect
of the Holocaust.

28
00:01:28.480 --> 00:01:31.440
turning genocide into
an industrial operation.

29
00:01:31.560 --> 00:01:33.920
He escaped justice after the war.

30
00:01:34.040 --> 00:01:36.600
He's still on the loose
somewhere. probably alive.

31
00:01:36.720 --> 00:01:38.480
but nobody could find out where.

32
00:01:38.600 --> 00:01:41.120
Then. in 1959. Israeli intelligence gets

33
00:01:41.240 --> 00:01:44.080
a credible tip that Eichmann
is living a quiet life

34
00:01:44.200 --> 00:01:46.440
in a suburb of Buenos Aires.

35
00:01:46.560 --> 00:01:48.880
The lead comes from a German refugee

36
00:01:49.000 --> 00:01:50.520
living in Argentina.

37
00:01:50.640 --> 00:01:52.640
Now. this guy's daughter
has been dating a guy

38
00:01:52.760 --> 00:01:54.880
who keeps bragging that
his dad used to have

39
00:01:55.000 --> 00:01:57.440
a really powerful position
in Nazi Germany.

40
00:01:57.560 --> 00:02:00.800
And the dad's name is Ricardo Klement.

41
00:02:00.920 --> 00:02:03.960
But the son goes by
the name Eichmann.

42
00:02:04.080 --> 00:02:05.776
The Israeli government
gets word of the fact

43
00:02:05.800 --> 00:02:08.320
that this person is
possibly Adolf Eichmann.

44
00:02:08.440 --> 00:02:10.240
If there's anyone left who can be

45
00:02:10.360 --> 00:02:12.480
brought to justice for
the crimes of the Holocaust.

46
00:02:12.600 --> 00:02:14.080
this is the man.

47
00:02:14.200 --> 00:02:15.480
There's one big obstacle

48
00:02:15.600 --> 00:02:17.440
Argentina.

49
00:02:17.560 --> 00:02:19.400
Israel and Argentina don't have

50
00:02:19.520 --> 00:02:21.120
a working extradition agreement.

51
00:02:21.240 --> 00:02:23.720
and Argentina has
a fascist-friendly government.

52
00:02:23.840 --> 00:02:25.280
So if Klement is Eichmann.

53
00:02:25.400 --> 00:02:27.160
there's no way
the Argentinian government

54
00:02:27.280 --> 00:02:29.040
is just gonna hand him over.

55
00:02:29.160 --> 00:02:32.680
To get their man.
Mossad decides to go rogue.

56
00:02:32.800 --> 00:02:34.360
A top secret group of Mossad agents

57
00:02:34.480 --> 00:02:36.040
is sent to Argentina.

58
00:02:36.160 --> 00:02:38.640
Their mission is to seek out
Klement and confirm that

59
00:02:38.760 --> 00:02:40.720
he is the same person as Eichmann.

60
00:02:40.840 --> 00:02:43.920
And if he is. to kidnap him
and bring him to Israel.

61
00:02:44.040 --> 00:02:46.000
You're not allowed
to do that kind of thing.

62
00:02:46.120 --> 00:02:49.080
That is a blatant disregard
for the sovereignty

63
00:02:49.200 --> 00:02:50.760
of another country.

64
00:02:50.880 --> 00:02:53.960
First. the Mossad team stalks their prey.

65
00:02:54.080 --> 00:02:56.520
They position agents
all along Klement's daily route

66
00:02:56.640 --> 00:02:58.600
to his job at a Mercedes-Benz plant.

67
00:02:58.720 --> 00:03:00.760
and they snap photographs
using cameras

68
00:03:00.880 --> 00:03:02.560
cleverly hidden inside briefcases.

69
00:03:02.680 --> 00:03:04.480
Their plan is to compare the pictures

70
00:03:04.600 --> 00:03:07.360
they take in Argentina against
wartime photos of Eichmann.

71
00:03:07.480 --> 00:03:10.560
Getting an image of Klement is easy.

72
00:03:10.680 --> 00:03:13.480
The hard part is finding
a picture of Eichmann.

73
00:03:13.600 --> 00:03:16.880
Toward the close of the war.
Eichmann deliberately destroyed

74
00:03:17.000 --> 00:03:18.880
every photograph he had of himself.

75
00:03:19.000 --> 00:03:21.200
Mossad have some grainy photographs

76
00:03:21.320 --> 00:03:24.480
from the pre-war period.
but what they are lacking

77
00:03:24.600 --> 00:03:27.640
is a photograph that
will provide a good view

78
00:03:27.760 --> 00:03:29.480
of his facial features.

79
00:03:29.600 --> 00:03:32.520
This is a problem
Mossad manages to solve.

80
00:03:32.640 --> 00:03:34.440
After the war. one agent

81
00:03:34.560 --> 00:03:36.840
seduced Eichmann's previous girlfriend.

82
00:03:36.960 --> 00:03:39.200
And in her personal albums.
they were able to find

83
00:03:39.320 --> 00:03:41.000
a picture of Eichmann from the war.

84
00:03:41.120 --> 00:03:42.760
To tell if these snaps

85
00:03:42.880 --> 00:03:46.040
taken over 20 years apart
are the same man.

86
00:03:46.160 --> 00:03:48.920
the Mossad team hones in on
the one feature

87
00:03:49.040 --> 00:03:51.920
the ear.

88
00:03:52.040 --> 00:03:55.400
The curves and ridges of the human ear

89
00:03:55.520 --> 00:03:58.360
are as distinct as a
fingerprint. so Mossad overlays

90
00:03:58.480 --> 00:04:01.080
the two photos and runs a painstaking

91
00:04:01.200 --> 00:04:02.880
ten-point comparison.

92
00:04:03.000 --> 00:04:06.240
And they discover that the
two men have an exact match.

93
00:04:06.360 --> 00:04:09.280
Ricardo Klement is Adolf Eichmann.

94
00:04:09.400 --> 00:04:12.400
Now. Mossad needs to capture him.

95
00:04:12.520 --> 00:04:14.280
On the evening of May 11th.

96
00:04:14.400 --> 00:04:16.640
as Eichmann steps off
his usual bus home.

97
00:04:16.760 --> 00:04:19.880
a man approaches him casually
and says. "Momentito. señor."

98
00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:22.079
Eichmann turns. and in that instant.

99
00:04:22.200 --> 00:04:24.960
he's tackled and dragged
into a waiting car.

100
00:04:25.080 --> 00:04:26.840
He is taken to a safe house

101
00:04:26.960 --> 00:04:28.560
on the outskirts of town.

102
00:04:28.680 --> 00:04:31.200
There. he is interrogated.
and he ultimately

103
00:04:31.320 --> 00:04:33.400
admits that he is Eichmann.

104
00:04:33.520 --> 00:04:36.240
Capturing Adolf Eichmann is one thing.

105
00:04:36.360 --> 00:04:38.000
Sneaking him out of the country

106
00:04:38.120 --> 00:04:40.720
without the Argentinian
authorities realizing.

107
00:04:40.840 --> 00:04:42.400
that's quite another.

108
00:04:42.520 --> 00:04:46.720
To do that. the Mossad team
crafts a daring escape plan.

109
00:04:46.840 --> 00:04:50.640
In ten days. a large official
Israeli delegation is scheduled

110
00:04:50.760 --> 00:04:52.240
to be in Buenos Aires.

111
00:04:52.360 --> 00:04:54.960
The agents' plan is to dress Eichmann

112
00:04:55.080 --> 00:04:58.000
in an airline crew uniform.
blend him into that crowd.

113
00:04:58.120 --> 00:05:01.120
slip him past security.
and fly home to Israel.

114
00:05:01.240 --> 00:05:03.520
Before arriving at the
airport. a doctor on the team

115
00:05:03.640 --> 00:05:05.480
heavily sedates Eichmann.

116
00:05:05.600 --> 00:05:07.320
They take him through the airport

117
00:05:07.440 --> 00:05:09.120
as part of their delegation. claiming that

118
00:05:09.240 --> 00:05:10.640
he's sick to everyone who's around.

119
00:05:10.680 --> 00:05:12.360
When the Israeli team gets to customs.

120
00:05:12.480 --> 00:05:14.160
they have a fake passport.

121
00:05:14.280 --> 00:05:17.000
That document was made
just a couple days ago.

122
00:05:17.120 --> 00:05:19.200
and they've done their best
to dirty it and crease it

123
00:05:19.240 --> 00:05:21.240
so it looks like a well-worn passport.

124
00:05:21.360 --> 00:05:23.040
but they don't know if it's going to work.

125
00:05:23.120 --> 00:05:25.320
It's almost as if the Border Patrol officer

126
00:05:25.440 --> 00:05:27.240
can sense that something isn't right.

127
00:05:29.520 --> 00:05:32.320
But ultimately. he clears
the group to get on the plane.

128
00:05:32.440 --> 00:05:35.480
At 12:05 on May 21st.

129
00:05:35.600 --> 00:05:38.320
the plane takes off carrying Eichmann.

130
00:05:38.440 --> 00:05:42.040
Two days later. Israeli Prime
Minister David Ben-Gurion

131
00:05:42.160 --> 00:05:44.200
makes a stunning announcement.

132
00:05:44.320 --> 00:05:47.520
Adolf Eichmann is in Israel.

133
00:05:47.640 --> 00:05:50.000
Argentina is beyond upset.

134
00:05:50.120 --> 00:05:52.280
They lodge a protest
at the United Nations.

135
00:05:52.400 --> 00:05:55.320
accusing Israel of violating
its national sovereignty

136
00:05:55.440 --> 00:05:57.520
and demand Eichmann's return.

137
00:05:57.640 --> 00:06:00.960
Israel refuses.
claiming private Nazi hunters

138
00:06:01.080 --> 00:06:02.880
carried out the operation.

139
00:06:03.000 --> 00:06:06.440
A year later. Eichmann
finally faces justice.

140
00:06:06.560 --> 00:06:08.280
Eichmann is put on trial.

141
00:06:08.400 --> 00:06:11.240
Survivors of the Holocaust
describe in detail

142
00:06:11.360 --> 00:06:14.720
the machines of murder
that Eichmann helped construct.

143
00:06:14.840 --> 00:06:17.920
He's found guilty
of crimes against humanity.

144
00:06:18.040 --> 00:06:20.880
Then. on May 31. 1962.

145
00:06:21.000 --> 00:06:23.640
Eichmann is executed by hanging.

146
00:06:23.760 --> 00:06:26.440
Only after 50 years does Israel finally

147
00:06:26.560 --> 00:06:28.880
drop the pretense
that Mossad had nothing

148
00:06:29.000 --> 00:06:30.400
to do with his capture.

149
00:06:30.520 --> 00:06:32.560
In 2012. the full truth is revealed

150
00:06:32.680 --> 00:06:36.360
when Mossad opens its archives
in an exhibition on Eichmann.

151
00:06:36.480 --> 00:06:38.280
They display the briefcase camera.

152
00:06:38.400 --> 00:06:41.480
the forged Israeli passport.
and even the ear comparison

153
00:06:41.600 --> 00:06:44.120
that confirmed his identity.

154
00:06:44.240 --> 00:06:46.640
Two decades after
Mossad sneak Eichmann out

155
00:06:46.760 --> 00:06:51.320
of Argentina. the CIA begins
its own smuggling operation

156
00:06:51.440 --> 00:06:54.960
to secretly funnel
an eye-watering $2 billion

157
00:06:55.080 --> 00:06:57.520
into the hands of anti-Soviet fighters.

158
00:06:57.640 --> 00:06:59.640
What follows is the most expensive

159
00:06:59.760 --> 00:07:04.960
and most consequential illicit
operation in U.S. history.

160
00:07:08.760 --> 00:07:12.560
In December 1979. the Soviet
Union launches a massive attack

161
00:07:12.680 --> 00:07:16.960
on Afghanistan to prop up
the Communist government

162
00:07:17.080 --> 00:07:20.000
by sending close to 100.000 troops.

163
00:07:20.120 --> 00:07:22.800
The Soviets seize the cities quickly.

164
00:07:22.920 --> 00:07:25.320
but out in the remote rural expanses.

165
00:07:25.440 --> 00:07:27.120
it's a whole different story.

166
00:07:27.240 --> 00:07:29.280
There. a coalition of Islamist fighters

167
00:07:29.400 --> 00:07:33.040
called the Mujahideen hold
their ground guerilla style.

168
00:07:33.160 --> 00:07:35.480
The CIA spots an opportunity.

169
00:07:35.600 --> 00:07:37.440
If they can drag out this fight.

170
00:07:37.560 --> 00:07:40.680
they could drain the power and
resources of the Soviet Army.

171
00:07:40.800 --> 00:07:43.120
So they kick start Operation Cyclone

172
00:07:43.240 --> 00:07:45.000
to support the Mujahideen.

173
00:07:45.120 --> 00:07:47.440
The problem is.
finding any guerrilla force

174
00:07:47.560 --> 00:07:51.200
fighting the Soviet Army
risks igniting World War III.

175
00:07:51.320 --> 00:07:54.920
and these are some highly
controversial new allies.

176
00:07:55.040 --> 00:07:58.160
The Mujahideen is funded
by the narcotics trade

177
00:07:58.280 --> 00:08:00.440
and are religious fundamentalists

178
00:08:00.560 --> 00:08:03.240
who hold very anti-Western views.

179
00:08:03.360 --> 00:08:06.800
Funding fundamentalist narco barons?

180
00:08:06.920 --> 00:08:08.640
Kind of a tough sell on Capitol Hill.

181
00:08:08.760 --> 00:08:10.320
To help win Congress's approval

182
00:08:10.440 --> 00:08:13.240
for this rogue operation.
the CIA teams up

183
00:08:13.360 --> 00:08:14.920
with an unlikely ally.

184
00:08:15.040 --> 00:08:18.440
The CIA turns to Texas
Congressman Charlie Wilson.

185
00:08:18.560 --> 00:08:21.360
He's this heavy drinking womanizer.

186
00:08:21.480 --> 00:08:23.920
but he's also politically savvy.

187
00:08:24.040 --> 00:08:26.640
Wilson's influence manages
to massively inflate

188
00:08:26.760 --> 00:08:29.680
the CIA's budget for Operation Cyclone.

189
00:08:29.800 --> 00:08:32.960
With Wilson's help. the
budget for Operation Cyclone

190
00:08:33.080 --> 00:08:37.799
balloons from $5 million to
more than $30 million by 1983.

191
00:08:37.919 --> 00:08:40.360
But to defeat a superpower.
the Mujahideen

192
00:08:40.480 --> 00:08:42.320
needs more than just money.

193
00:08:42.440 --> 00:08:47.800
They need something the CIA
can't send them: Firepower.

194
00:08:47.920 --> 00:08:49.400
If the CIA flooded

195
00:08:49.520 --> 00:08:51.160
American weapons into Afghanistan.

196
00:08:51.280 --> 00:08:52.800
that would be an open provocation

197
00:08:52.920 --> 00:08:53.920
against the Soviets.

198
00:08:53.960 --> 00:08:56.040
Also. the Mujahideen

199
00:08:56.160 --> 00:08:58.200
don't know how to use
American weaponry.

200
00:08:58.320 --> 00:09:00.040
They are trained on Soviet weapons.

201
00:09:00.160 --> 00:09:01.480
Somehow the Americans have to get

202
00:09:01.560 --> 00:09:04.200
their hands on a cache
of Soviet weapons

203
00:09:04.320 --> 00:09:06.200
that can't be traced back to them.

204
00:09:06.320 --> 00:09:08.760
In 1983. this challenge is handed

205
00:09:08.880 --> 00:09:13.280
to a renegade CIA agent.
a man named Gust Avrakotos.

206
00:09:13.400 --> 00:09:16.280
also known as "Dr. Dirty."

207
00:09:16.400 --> 00:09:20.040
Avrakotos is a blunt.
foul-mouthed agency fixer.

208
00:09:20.160 --> 00:09:21.960
known for bending the rules.

209
00:09:22.080 --> 00:09:24.360
He knows that Egypt
has recently switched

210
00:09:24.480 --> 00:09:27.320
its alignment from the USSR to the U.S.

211
00:09:27.440 --> 00:09:31.000
Avrakotos feels there could
be a massive supply

212
00:09:31.120 --> 00:09:33.800
of Soviet weapons in Egypt.

213
00:09:33.920 --> 00:09:35.760
So he flies to Cairo.

214
00:09:35.880 --> 00:09:37.960
where he gets the red carpet treatment

215
00:09:38.080 --> 00:09:41.640
thanks to Congressman Charlie Wilson.

216
00:09:41.760 --> 00:09:43.440
The Egyptians have
already been softened up

217
00:09:43.520 --> 00:09:46.200
by a visit from Wilson.
who allegedly brought

218
00:09:46.320 --> 00:09:48.440
his own personal belly dancer to perform

219
00:09:48.560 --> 00:09:50.280
for the defense minister.

220
00:09:50.400 --> 00:09:52.360
Whatever it is she did during that dance.

221
00:09:52.480 --> 00:09:53.920
it seems to have worked.

222
00:09:56.280 --> 00:10:00.480
The defense minister gives
Avrakotos a personal VIP tour

223
00:10:00.600 --> 00:10:04.000
of all the Egyptian defense installations

224
00:10:04.120 --> 00:10:05.800
that house the Soviet matériel.

225
00:10:05.920 --> 00:10:07.520
Amongst this hoard of weaponry.

226
00:10:07.640 --> 00:10:10.720
Gust spots a weapon that
could truly tip the scales...

227
00:10:10.840 --> 00:10:13.880
54 Katyusha rocket launchers.

228
00:10:14.000 --> 00:10:17.640
The Katyusha is a 122-millimeter rocket

229
00:10:17.760 --> 00:10:21.240
that would give the Mujahideen
long-range firepower

230
00:10:21.360 --> 00:10:24.240
for the very first time.

231
00:10:24.360 --> 00:10:27.960
Now. it's not accurate enough
to take out helicopters.

232
00:10:28.080 --> 00:10:31.280
but it can hit the Soviet bases
that they fly from.

233
00:10:31.400 --> 00:10:34.800
Avrakotos buys everything
the Egyptians have.

234
00:10:34.920 --> 00:10:38.840
His next challenge is to get
these weapons over 2.000 miles

235
00:10:38.960 --> 00:10:40.680
from Egypt to Afghanistan.

236
00:10:40.800 --> 00:10:43.480
Believe it or not. the best way to get

237
00:10:43.600 --> 00:10:46.080
a rocket launcher
to Afghanistan undetected

238
00:10:46.200 --> 00:10:49.800
is to strap it to a camel.

239
00:10:49.920 --> 00:10:52.840
Gust engineers a massive
covert supply chain.

240
00:10:52.960 --> 00:10:55.480
First. ships carry the arms from Egypt

241
00:10:55.600 --> 00:10:58.240
through the Suez Canal into Pakistan.

242
00:10:58.360 --> 00:11:01.000
And then the weapons complete
the journey over the border

243
00:11:01.120 --> 00:11:04.480
into Afghanistan on
traditional camel caravans.

244
00:11:04.600 --> 00:11:07.520
At its height. some 300.000 guerrillas

245
00:11:07.640 --> 00:11:10.040
wield CIA-sourced weapons.

246
00:11:10.160 --> 00:11:12.760
By the late 1980s. the CIA

247
00:11:12.880 --> 00:11:15.200
is channeling over $600 million

248
00:11:15.320 --> 00:11:17.160
annually into Afghanistan.

249
00:11:17.280 --> 00:11:21.120
This flood of cash
and arms turns the tide.

250
00:11:21.240 --> 00:11:22.960
The Soviet Union officially withdraws

251
00:11:23.080 --> 00:11:25.680
on February 15. 1989.

252
00:11:25.800 --> 00:11:28.680
The drain on the Soviets was immense.

253
00:11:28.800 --> 00:11:33.480
Billions were spent.
15.000 Soviet soldiers died.

254
00:11:33.600 --> 00:11:36.680
and scholars say this was
one of the pressure points

255
00:11:36.800 --> 00:11:39.040
that eventually led to the collapse

256
00:11:39.160 --> 00:11:40.840
of the Soviet Union.

257
00:11:40.960 --> 00:11:43.280
