stakes gamble has paid off.

519
00:23:10.760 --> 00:23:13.400
London rolls out pre-written headlines.

520
00:23:13.520 --> 00:23:16.200
"Navy patrols on routine duty seized

521
00:23:16.320 --> 00:23:18.040
the three ships legally."

522
00:23:18.160 --> 00:23:21.240
The Spanish are furious
over the incursion.

523
00:23:21.360 --> 00:23:23.040
but there's no proof that Britain

524
00:23:23.160 --> 00:23:24.960
has broken international law.

525
00:23:25.080 --> 00:23:26.480
With this mission.

526
00:23:26.600 --> 00:23:28.480
Churchill is sending a powerful message.

527
00:23:28.600 --> 00:23:31.880
He is acknowledging that the
Germans are bending the rules.

528
00:23:32.000 --> 00:23:35.320
and he's also telling them.
I'm gonna bend the rules too.

529
00:23:35.440 --> 00:23:37.320
Two can play at that game.

530
00:23:37.440 --> 00:23:39.200
For over 40 years.

531
00:23:39.320 --> 00:23:40.800
the British maintain the cover story.

532
00:23:40.920 --> 00:23:43.080
Only when Spain's fascist government

533
00:23:43.200 --> 00:23:45.520
is removed from power
does British intelligence

534
00:23:45.640 --> 00:23:48.000
begin to declassify the truth.

535
00:23:48.120 --> 00:23:51.320
The astonishing story
of Operation Postmaster

536
00:23:51.440 --> 00:23:52.640
is finally revealed.

537
00:23:55.880 --> 00:23:59.400
All rogue missions ignore the rules.

538
00:23:59.520 --> 00:24:02.400
Our next story also ignores the risk.

539
00:24:02.520 --> 00:24:05.760
To uncover the horrors
of a new Nazi prison camp.

540
00:24:05.880 --> 00:24:09.240
one spy walks inside willingly.

541
00:24:09.360 --> 00:24:12.120
then escapes it
to tell the world what he saw.

542
00:24:12.240 --> 00:24:14.640
That camp is Auschwitz.

543
00:24:17.480 --> 00:24:19.160
It's 1940.

544
00:24:19.280 --> 00:24:21.720
Poland has been occupied by Nazi

545
00:24:21.840 --> 00:24:23.480
and Soviet forces for about a year

546
00:24:23.600 --> 00:24:24.840
when whispers begin circulating

547
00:24:24.880 --> 00:24:26.680
about a new prison camp being built

548
00:24:26.800 --> 00:24:28.960
in the south near the town of Oswiecim.

549
00:24:29.080 --> 00:24:31.320
Oswiecim will ultimately become known

550
00:24:31.440 --> 00:24:33.280
as the concentration camp

551
00:24:33.400 --> 00:24:35.440
and then eventually
the extermination center

552
00:24:35.560 --> 00:24:37.120
of Auschwitz-Birkenau.

553
00:24:37.240 --> 00:24:38.800
Auschwitz is synonymous with evil.

554
00:24:38.920 --> 00:24:40.960
It's the epicenter of the Holocaust.

555
00:24:41.080 --> 00:24:43.720
where over a million people
were systematically murdered.

556
00:24:43.840 --> 00:24:46.200
But back in mid-1940.

557
00:24:46.320 --> 00:24:50.440
the name of this camp and
its true purpose is a mystery.

558
00:24:50.560 --> 00:24:52.560
All the Polish people know

559
00:24:52.680 --> 00:24:55.840
is that the Germans have taken
over some old army barracks

560
00:24:55.960 --> 00:24:59.000
and converted them
into a detention facility.

561
00:24:59.120 --> 00:25:01.480
But when the first prisoners arrive there.

562
00:25:01.600 --> 00:25:04.360
alarming reports start to leak out.

563
00:25:04.480 --> 00:25:07.280
There are tales of murder. torture.

564
00:25:07.400 --> 00:25:08.920
and horrific experiments.

565
00:25:09.040 --> 00:25:11.240
The Polish resistance decides

566
00:25:11.360 --> 00:25:13.096
it needs urgent answers
about what's going on

567
00:25:13.120 --> 00:25:14.680
behind the barbed wire.

568
00:25:14.800 --> 00:25:18.400
So one 39-year-old officer
named Witold Pilecki

569
00:25:18.520 --> 00:25:20.680
volunteers for an incredible mission.

570
00:25:20.800 --> 00:25:22.920
Witold Pilecki is a former army lieutenant

571
00:25:23.040 --> 00:25:25.640
who hates the Nazis and will stop

572
00:25:25.760 --> 00:25:27.680
at nothing to sabotage them.

573
00:25:27.800 --> 00:25:31.040
He literally volunteers to
go undercover as a prisoner

574
00:25:31.160 --> 00:25:32.720
to the Nazi prisoner camp.

575
00:25:32.840 --> 00:25:34.640
Once there. he means
to collect intelligence.

576
00:25:34.760 --> 00:25:37.360
build a resistance network
to smuggle in food

577
00:25:37.480 --> 00:25:38.680
and medicine for the inmates.

578
00:25:38.800 --> 00:25:40.640
His plan is so extreme

579
00:25:40.760 --> 00:25:42.480
not everyone is on board.

580
00:25:42.600 --> 00:25:45.320
Some of Pilecki's leaders
don't know how bad things are

581
00:25:45.440 --> 00:25:47.720
inside this concentration camp.
but they're worried that

582
00:25:47.840 --> 00:25:49.160
it's basically a suicide run.

583
00:25:49.280 --> 00:25:51.480
The plan is so far
outside normal procedures

584
00:25:51.600 --> 00:25:53.680
that it's incredible the Polish resistance

585
00:25:53.800 --> 00:25:55.920
doesn't simply shut it down.

586
00:25:56.040 --> 00:25:58.600
In late summer. Pilecki is finally

587
00:25:58.720 --> 00:26:01.040
granted permission
to head into Auschwitz.

588
00:26:01.160 --> 00:26:03.200
But he can't just walk up
and knock on the door.

589
00:26:03.320 --> 00:26:07.320
He needs to be transported
there as a genuine prisoner.

590
00:26:07.440 --> 00:26:09.176
To make sure his military
record doesn't draw

591
00:26:09.200 --> 00:26:12.400
the attention of the Gestapo.
he takes on a false identity.

592
00:26:12.520 --> 00:26:14.240
Tomasz Serafinski.

593
00:26:14.360 --> 00:26:16.480
Then. he deliberately gets himself

594
00:26:16.600 --> 00:26:18.480
rounded up by the German military police

595
00:26:18.600 --> 00:26:20.400
in the streets of Warsaw.

596
00:26:20.520 --> 00:26:22.560
Those arrested could be
taken anywhere in the Reich.

597
00:26:22.640 --> 00:26:24.760
And his plan is to
essentially just hope that

598
00:26:24.880 --> 00:26:26.360
he gets sent to Auschwitz.

599
00:26:26.480 --> 00:26:29.360
Three days later.
Pilecki's gamble pays off.

600
00:26:29.480 --> 00:26:32.200
He enters the camp underneath
the now infamous sign

601
00:26:32.320 --> 00:26:34.120
that reads "arbeit macht frei."

602
00:26:34.240 --> 00:26:36.120
"work will set you free."

603
00:26:36.240 --> 00:26:38.640
Witold Pilecki is the only

604
00:26:38.760 --> 00:26:42.520
known person to have ever
entered Auschwitz by choice.

605
00:26:42.640 --> 00:26:45.400
Now he's prisoner 4859.

606
00:26:45.520 --> 00:26:48.960
In the camp. Pilecki
endures backbreaking labor.

607
00:26:49.080 --> 00:26:52.760
conditions so harsh that
a prisoner's life expectancy

608
00:26:52.880 --> 00:26:54.840
is measured in weeks. not months.

609
00:26:54.960 --> 00:26:58.160
He keeps his head down. but
he begins to build a network.

610
00:26:58.280 --> 00:27:00.720
Pilecki recruits other
prisoners inside the camp.

611
00:27:00.840 --> 00:27:02.320
and they start organizing a group

612
00:27:02.440 --> 00:27:03.840
to distribute food and clothing.

613
00:27:03.960 --> 00:27:06.720
And they even undertake
small acts of sabotage.

614
00:27:06.840 --> 00:27:11.640
Against all odds. Pilecki's
daring mission is paying off.

615
00:27:11.760 --> 00:27:15.440
But in March 1942. everything changes

616
00:27:15.560 --> 00:27:19.200
when Auschwitz transforms
from a brutal work camp

617
00:27:19.320 --> 00:27:23.000
into an extermination machine.

618
00:27:23.120 --> 00:27:25.880
In the spring of 1942. Nazi leaders begin

619
00:27:26.000 --> 00:27:28.360
to enact their Final Solution.

620
00:27:28.480 --> 00:27:31.160
This is a genocidal
blueprint for wiping out

621
00:27:31.280 --> 00:27:33.520
all of Europe's Jews.

622
00:27:33.640 --> 00:27:35.680
Pilecki is witness to the opening stages

623
00:27:35.800 --> 00:27:37.200
of the Holocaust.

624
00:27:37.320 --> 00:27:39.840
He sees trains arriving.
coming and going.

625
00:27:39.960 --> 00:27:44.160
He sees Jewish men. women. and
children being dropped off.

626
00:27:44.280 --> 00:27:47.000
And then he sees
billowing clouds of smoke.

627
00:27:47.120 --> 00:27:49.440
indicating that
they have been incinerated.

628
00:27:49.560 --> 00:27:51.840
Faced with this horror. Pilecki knows

629
00:27:51.960 --> 00:27:54.360
the world must hear the truth.

630
00:27:54.480 --> 00:27:58.480
It's a message so crucial
he must deliver it in person.

631
00:27:58.600 --> 00:28:03.000
So two years and seven months
after breaking into Auschwitz.

632
00:28:03.120 --> 00:28:04.920
Pilecki plots his escape.

633
00:28:05.040 --> 00:28:07.560
Through his network.
Pilecki and two co-conspirators

634
00:28:07.680 --> 00:28:12.360
slowly gather false papers.
civilian clothes. money.

635
00:28:12.480 --> 00:28:15.440
and even cyanide. which they
will use on themselves

636
00:28:15.560 --> 00:28:16.960
if they do get captured.

637
00:28:17.080 --> 00:28:19.080
Pilecki bribes a guard to transfer him

638
00:28:19.200 --> 00:28:21.520
to the camp bakery located just outside

639
00:28:21.640 --> 00:28:26.240
the main perimeter. one of the
least secure areas of the camp.

640
00:28:26.360 --> 00:28:29.360
The night of April 26. 1943.

641
00:28:29.480 --> 00:28:31.280
they make their move.

642
00:28:31.400 --> 00:28:34.640
At 2:00 a.m.. the three men
force open the bakery door

643
00:28:34.760 --> 00:28:36.200
and sprint into the darkness.

644
00:28:36.320 --> 00:28:39.560
The alarm sounds.
gunfire goes off behind them.

645
00:28:39.680 --> 00:28:42.480
but somehow they vanish
into the woods.

646
00:28:42.600 --> 00:28:48.960
Then they make a grueling
60-mile journey on foot

647
00:28:49.080 --> 00:28:51.440
until they reach a resistance safe house.

648
00:28:51.560 --> 00:28:53.640
Shortly after. Pilecki hand writes

649
00:28:53.760 --> 00:28:55.880
his 104-page mission report.

650
00:28:56.000 --> 00:28:57.760
It's a landmark document.

651
00:28:57.880 --> 00:28:59.840
Pilecki writes the first eyewitness

652
00:28:59.960 --> 00:29:01.080
account of the Holocaust.

653
00:29:01.200 --> 00:29:02.600
It's the first time the Allies

654
00:29:02.720 --> 00:29:04.120
really understand what's going on.

655
00:29:04.240 --> 00:29:06.080
but they're helpless to do anything.

656
00:29:06.200 --> 00:29:09.720
It's not until January of 1945
that the Soviet troops arrive

657
00:29:09.840 --> 00:29:11.560
and finally liberate Auschwitz.

658
00:29:11.680 --> 00:29:14.680
Pilecki survives
the war. but in the aftermath.

659
00:29:14.800 --> 00:29:17.640
he faces a new. deadly challenge.

660
00:29:17.760 --> 00:29:19.280
Two years after Germany's defeat.

661
00:29:19.400 --> 00:29:21.240
Poland falls under Soviet control.

662
00:29:21.360 --> 00:29:24.480
Now Pilecki has to fight for
his country all over again.

663
00:29:24.600 --> 00:29:26.840
But this time. it doesn't go as well.

664
00:29:26.960 --> 00:29:28.800
He's arrested by the
Communists for organizing

665
00:29:28.920 --> 00:29:30.160
acts of resistance.

666
00:29:30.280 --> 00:29:32.400
He's tried. convicted.

667
00:29:32.520 --> 00:29:34.760
and then in 1948. he is executed.

668
00:29:34.880 --> 00:29:37.320
After his death. the Soviets expunged.

669
00:29:37.440 --> 00:29:40.040
Pilecki's bravery from Polish history.

670
00:29:40.160 --> 00:29:42.320
His incredible mission
to reveal the horrors

671
00:29:42.440 --> 00:29:44.320
of Auschwitz is buried...

672
00:29:44.440 --> 00:29:48.480
until 2000. a decade after
the Soviet Union collapses.

673
00:29:48.600 --> 00:29:51.560
when his eyewitness report
is finally published.

674
00:29:51.680 --> 00:29:54.840
In 2006. Poland
posthumously honors Pilecki

675
00:29:54.960 --> 00:29:58.320
with the Order of the White
Eagle. their highest award.

676
00:29:58.440 --> 00:30:01.000
Recognition of a spy
who broke all the rules

677
00:30:01.120 --> 00:30:03.880
to walk into a hell on Earth

678
00:30:04.000 --> 00:30:05.480
and tell the world what he saw.

679
00:30:08.600 --> 00:30:10.456
In the last 150 years.
more than 60 national leaders

680
00:30:10.480 --> 00:30:12.240
have been assassinated.

681
00:30:12.360 --> 00:30:14.520
Those responsible are usually radicals.

682
00:30:14.640 --> 00:30:16.360
rebels. or lone gunmen.

683
00:30:16.480 --> 00:30:19.240
But behind this plot to kill
a democratically elected

684
00:30:19.360 --> 00:30:22.360
prime minister is the CIA.

685
00:30:25.720 --> 00:30:27.920
On June 30. 1960.

686
00:30:28.040 --> 00:30:29.880
the African nation of the Congo.

687
00:30:30.000 --> 00:30:33.400
now known as the DRC.
declares independence

688
00:30:33.520 --> 00:30:36.400
after decades of colonial rule by Belgium.

689
00:30:36.520 --> 00:30:39.600
The country's first ever prime
minister. Patrice Lumumba.

690
00:30:39.720 --> 00:30:42.360
promises that from now on.
the Congolese people

691
00:30:42.480 --> 00:30:46.680
will control their own land.
including its mineral wealth.

692
00:30:46.800 --> 00:30:48.760
The Congolese are euphoric.

693
00:30:48.880 --> 00:30:50.760
In Belgium. they're seething.

694
00:30:50.880 --> 00:30:52.320
The Congo is massive.

695
00:30:52.440 --> 00:30:54.240
It's about the size of Western Europe.

696
00:30:54.360 --> 00:30:57.640
and it is absolutely packed with minerals.

697
00:30:57.760 --> 00:31:00.600
There's copper. there's
cobalt. there's uranium...

698
00:31:00.720 --> 00:31:03.880
all resources that Belgian
corporations have been mining

699
00:31:04.000 --> 00:31:06.360
to fuel their industries for generations.

700
00:31:06.480 --> 00:31:08.680
Belgium immediately moves to reclaim

701
00:31:08.800 --> 00:31:10.760
control of this wealth.

702
00:31:10.880 --> 00:31:12.880
It incites a mineral-rich southern region

703
00:31:13.000 --> 00:31:16.480
known as Katanga to
break away from the Congo.

704
00:31:16.600 --> 00:31:18.240
They select a local politician

705
00:31:18.360 --> 00:31:21.240
to be a puppet leader
and send in Belgian troops

706
00:31:21.360 --> 00:31:22.880
to support him.

707
00:31:23.000 --> 00:31:24.640
To hold his country together.

708
00:31:24.760 --> 00:31:27.160
Lumumba asks the U.S. for military aid.

709
00:31:27.280 --> 00:31:30.000
When they refuse. he turns to the East.

710
00:31:30.120 --> 00:31:32.080
Lumumba reaches out
to the Soviet Union.

711
00:31:32.200 --> 00:31:34.760
and they give him weapons and advisors.

712
00:31:34.880 --> 00:31:37.680
Now. for America. that crosses a line.

713
00:31:37.800 --> 00:31:41.240
Washington now
sees Lumumba as a threat.

714
00:31:41.360 --> 00:31:43.280
potentially spreading
Communism throughout

715
00:31:43.400 --> 00:31:44.800
the African continent.

716
00:31:44.920 --> 00:31:47.040
The CIA director. Allen Dulles.

717
00:31:47.160 --> 00:31:49.400
demands his urgent removal.

718
00:31:49.520 --> 00:31:52.320
They wanna take out the
democratically elected leader

719
00:31:52.440 --> 00:31:55.240
of a sovereign nation. a flagrant violation

720
00:31:55.360 --> 00:31:57.040
of international law.

721
00:31:57.160 --> 00:31:59.840
The man who gets
the task is Larry Devlin.

722
00:31:59.960 --> 00:32:04.240
CIA Station Chief at Congo's
capital. Léopoldville.

723
00:32:04.360 --> 00:32:07.640
Devlin decides he's gonna
remove Lumumba from power

724
00:32:07.760 --> 00:32:09.840
by orchestrating chaos.

725
00:32:09.960 --> 00:32:11.760
He funds the opposition.

726
00:32:11.880 --> 00:32:13.840
He bankrolls demonstrators.

727
00:32:13.960 --> 00:32:16.600
And he spreads
anti-Lumumba propaganda.

728
00:32:16.720 --> 00:32:19.280
Then he sets his sights on the military.

729
00:32:19.400 --> 00:32:21.840
The CIA starts paying off colonels

730
00:32:21.960 --> 00:32:24.120
in the army for their loyalty.

731
00:32:24.240 --> 00:32:26.200
Soon. the country is in chaos.

732
00:32:26.320 --> 00:32:29.440
And now they encourage a new
leader to take advantage.

733
00:32:29.560 --> 00:32:32.440
Colonel Mobutu places
Lumumba under house arrest.

734
00:32:32.560 --> 00:32:35.000
and the military seizes control
of all of the elements

735
00:32:35.120 --> 00:32:36.640
of government power.

736
00:32:36.760 --> 00:32:38.136
But for the CIA. that's not enough.

737
00:32:38.160 --> 00:32:40.760
They need a more permanent solution.

738
00:32:40.880 --> 00:32:44.200
As long as Lumumba is alive.
he remains a powerful symbol

739
00:32:44.320 --> 00:32:46.000
with huge support among the people.

740
00:32:46.120 --> 00:32:47.600
The CIA needs him gone.

741
00:32:47.720 --> 00:32:49.600
But if Devlin is going to solve

742
00:32:49.720 --> 00:32:52.320
the problem of Lumumba.
he needs to do it fast.

743
00:32:52.440 --> 00:32:54.800
There has been an election
in the United States

744
00:32:54.920 --> 00:32:57.240
and a concern that JFK could soon

745
00:32:57.360 --> 00:32:59.760
call for Lumumba's release.

746
00:32:59.880 --> 00:33:02.440
Devlin's bosses suggest poison.

747
00:33:02.560 --> 00:33:05.520
But he thinks that might get
traced back to the agency.

748
00:33:05.640 --> 00:33:09.840
Then he figures Lumumba has
many enemies besides the CIA.

749
00:33:09.960 --> 00:33:13.480
so why not get one of them
to do the job for him?

750
00:33:13.600 --> 00:33:15.840
Larry Devlin settles in on a plan.

751
00:33:15.960 --> 00:33:19.600
and that is to deliver Lumumba
to his political enemies

752
00:33:19.720 --> 00:33:21.240
in the province of Katanga.

753
00:33:21.360 --> 00:33:25.200
and there. his execution
is pretty much guaranteed.

754
00:33:25.320 --> 00:33:27.640
But Persuading
the Congo's many factions

755
00:33:27.760 --> 00:33:29.960
to sign up to this plan isn't easy

756
00:33:30.080 --> 00:33:31.400
without attracting attention.

757
00:33:31.520 --> 00:33:33.640
Devlin needs to coordinate

758
00:33:33.760 --> 00:33:36.160
with a lot of different groups
in the Republic of Congo.

759
00:33:36.280 --> 00:33:39.480
but he's prominent enough
that he needs an excuse

760
00:33:39.600 --> 00:33:42.000
for why he can move around the country.

761
00:33:42.120 --> 00:33:44.480
Luckily for him.
the perfect smokescreen is

762
00:33:44.600 --> 00:33:47.040
on its way. a living legend.

763
00:33:47.160 --> 00:33:50.320
In October 1960. a plane touches down

764
00:33:50.440 --> 00:33:52.360
at the Léopoldville airport.

765
00:33:52.480 --> 00:33:56.080
And out steps none other
than Louis Armstrong.

766
00:33:56.200 --> 00:34:01.080
Satchmo. arguably America's
first truly global superstar.

767
00:34:01.200 --> 00:34:04.320
has come to play in the Congo
where his concerts draw

768
00:34:04.440 --> 00:34:07.160
crowds of over 100.000 people.

769
00:34:07.280 --> 00:34:09.679
For the CIA. the timing is perfect.

770
00:34:09.800 --> 00:34:12.800
Devlin hosts Armstrong at
the U.S. embassy facilities

771
00:34:12.920 --> 00:34:14.800
and can use the concert schedule

772
00:34:14.920 --> 00:34:16.639
to jet around the country.

773
00:34:16.760 --> 00:34:18.320
It's argued that. under the guise

774
00:34:18.440 --> 00:34:19.960
of those tours logistics.

775
00:34:20.080 --> 00:34:22.760
Devlin meets Lumumba's
enemies in Katanga

776
00:34:22.880 --> 00:34:24.520
to plot his execution.

777
00:34:24.639 --> 00:34:27.480
All the while. Armstrong has no idea

778
00:34:27.600 --> 00:34:32.280
