800
00:35:33.320 --> 00:35:37.120
of just how far
the CIA's manipulations went.

801
00:35:37.240 --> 00:35:41.720
right to the CIA's use of
Louis Armstrong's Congo tour

802
00:35:41.840 --> 00:35:42.840
as a smoke screen.

803
00:35:45.760 --> 00:35:47.320
From the 1950s to the 1970s.

804
00:35:47.440 --> 00:35:49.400
the Federal Bureau of Investigation

805
00:35:49.520 --> 00:35:52.040
under the iron reign of J. Edgar Hoover

806
00:35:52.160 --> 00:35:54.760
runs a top secret illegal operation

807
00:35:54.880 --> 00:35:57.160
targeting thousands of U.S. citizens.

808
00:35:57.280 --> 00:35:59.160
The only reason we know about it

809
00:35:59.280 --> 00:36:01.600
is because eight ordinary Americans

810
00:36:01.720 --> 00:36:04.880
pulled off one extraordinary heist.

811
00:36:08.960 --> 00:36:12.240
By 1956. J. Edgar Hoover
has been running the FBI

812
00:36:12.360 --> 00:36:14.880
for over three decades.

813
00:36:15.000 --> 00:36:17.600
For him. the real threat
to America's security

814
00:36:17.720 --> 00:36:20.040
isn't organized crime or bank robbers.

815
00:36:20.160 --> 00:36:24.120
it's ideas. political movements
that threaten the system.

816
00:36:24.240 --> 00:36:26.560
particularly Communism.

817
00:36:26.680 --> 00:36:29.000
He wants to root out these
groups and neutralize them.

818
00:36:29.120 --> 00:36:30.720
No holds barred.

819
00:36:30.840 --> 00:36:32.240
Hoover's problem is.

820
00:36:32.360 --> 00:36:34.280
the courts keep getting in his way.

821
00:36:34.400 --> 00:36:36.960
Hoover is willing to use illegal wiretaps.

822
00:36:37.080 --> 00:36:38.840
bugging. intercepting mail.

823
00:36:38.960 --> 00:36:41.840
He believes that these tools
and tactics are fair game.

824
00:36:41.960 --> 00:36:43.960
But the courts insist on warrants.

825
00:36:44.080 --> 00:36:45.960
They want constitutional protections.

826
00:36:46.080 --> 00:36:48.960
Hoover sees these as
operational inconveniences.

827
00:36:49.080 --> 00:36:53.320
So in 1956. he
decides to circumvent the law

828
00:36:53.440 --> 00:36:57.320
with a new classified
operation he calls COINTELPRO.

829
00:36:57.440 --> 00:37:00.120
short for Counterintelligence Program.

830
00:37:00.240 --> 00:37:03.840
Hoover creates a program
to try to monitor the behavior

831
00:37:03.960 --> 00:37:05.760
of potential dissident groups.

832
00:37:05.880 --> 00:37:09.120
He also starts having agents
infiltrate them and push

833
00:37:09.240 --> 00:37:12.240
more radical activity than
they had previously espoused.

834
00:37:12.360 --> 00:37:16.480
which will then justify the FBI
in suppressing those groups.

835
00:37:16.600 --> 00:37:18.480
This is an illegal operation

836
00:37:18.600 --> 00:37:21.520
targeting U.S. citizens on American soil.

837
00:37:21.640 --> 00:37:24.000
and it grows fast.

838
00:37:24.120 --> 00:37:27.200
By the 1960s. Hoover expands
the program's scope

839
00:37:27.320 --> 00:37:28.960
to civil rights leaders and opponents

840
00:37:29.080 --> 00:37:30.760
of the war in Vietnam.

841
00:37:30.880 --> 00:37:33.120
Any voice speaking out
against the status quo.

842
00:37:33.240 --> 00:37:35.800
Hoover calls it subversive
and unleashes his agents.

843
00:37:35.920 --> 00:37:37.760
One activist is dead center

844
00:37:37.880 --> 00:37:41.080
Dr. Martin Luther King Jr.

845
00:37:41.200 --> 00:37:42.920
At this time. Martin Luther King

846
00:37:43.040 --> 00:37:45.760
is the most prominent voice
in the Civil Rights movement.

847
00:37:45.880 --> 00:37:50.240
His profile and influence make
him a key target for Hoover.

848
00:37:50.360 --> 00:37:53.480
In 1962. Hoover instructs COINTELPRO

849
00:37:53.600 --> 00:37:56.560
