898
00:39:57.800 --> 00:40:01.400
The group find hundreds
of classified pages.

899
00:40:01.520 --> 00:40:05.000
They take all this information
and walk out into the night.

900
00:40:05.120 --> 00:40:06.840
Back at a safe house.

901
00:40:06.960 --> 00:40:09.760
they sift through over 1.000 pages.

902
00:40:09.880 --> 00:40:14.080
and they come across the
critical name. "COINTELPRO."

903
00:40:14.200 --> 00:40:17.240
The activists have
uncovered extensive details

904
00:40:17.360 --> 00:40:19.280
of Hoover's illegal war.

905
00:40:19.400 --> 00:40:21.720
The question now. is any journalist

906
00:40:21.840 --> 00:40:23.680
brave enough to take on Hoover

907
00:40:23.800 --> 00:40:25.800
and publish what they've found?

908
00:40:25.920 --> 00:40:27.720
The burglars mail copies
of some of the most

909
00:40:27.800 --> 00:40:29.640
incriminating documents to members

910
00:40:29.760 --> 00:40:31.360
of the press and politicians.

911
00:40:31.480 --> 00:40:34.640
Most of the recipients
of this classified material

912
00:40:34.760 --> 00:40:37.240
are terrified at the prospect
of publishing it

913
00:40:37.360 --> 00:40:40.520
because publishing classified
documents is a crime.

914
00:40:40.640 --> 00:40:42.080
Only Betty Medsger. a journalist

915
00:40:42.200 --> 00:40:44.160
for "The Washington Post."
has the courage

916
00:40:44.280 --> 00:40:46.000
to publish the story.

917
00:40:46.120 --> 00:40:50.000
And when it hits the press.
the country absolutely erupts.

918
00:40:50.120 --> 00:40:52.240
Hoover defends his actions as needed

919
00:40:52.360 --> 00:40:54.240
